message.content:
cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.AR, cs.SC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing software for decomposing sparse tensors that is portable and performant on a variety of multicore, manycore, and GPU computing architectures. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of the matricized tensor times Khatri-Rao product (MTTKRP) which is a key kernel in canonical polyadic tensor decomposition. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as the paper discusses the optimization of the MTTKRP algorithm to reduce atomic-write contention. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the performance of the implementation on different architectures. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on symbolic computation, but it does involve mathematical computations and optimization.
